<BaseLayout
  title="About — Vincent Del Toral"
  description="About Vincent Del Toral — software engineer with 7 years of experience, now consulting directly with businesses."
>
  <section class="section section-narrow">
    <div class="reveal">
      <h1 style="font-size: 2.4rem; margin-bottom: 32px;">About</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="about-content reveal" data-delay="100">
      <p>I spent seven years as a software engineer — backend systems, full-stack apps, the whole range. I worked on teams building products that people actually used, and I got good at taking messy requirements and turning them into clean, working software.</p>

      <p>In 2022, I stepped away from full-time roles. I'd been building things for other people's companies long enough to know that the work I enjoyed most was solving specific, tangible problems — not sitting in standups or navigating corporate roadmaps.</p>

      <p>Now I work directly with business owners. There's no team, no project manager, no overhead. You tell me what you need, I figure out how to build it, and I get it done. Most of the people I work with aren't technical — they just know something in their business could work better, and they need someone to make that happen.</p>

      <p>If that sounds like what you're looking for, I'd like to hear about it.</p>

      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Get In Touch</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
